I lost the love of my life in May. Its been rough. I'm poly and my main partner is married. His biological family only knows I'm a close friend but hes open to everyone he can be open with. My other partner was the first relationship I got to meet the family and it all was in the open. I lasted 5 months. It was devastating to go through my loss and grieve. I still have my bad days. But I have to keep going. I've dated others since and have someone else. He's nice. It's not the same. I miss Sean so much. But he's not good for me if he decided to not be there.

Take it day by day Jeffree. Every month I listen to Sia's Rainbow song and I can see how far I've come since. Heck I even forgot tomorrow would have been our 13 month anniversary. Go to therapy. The first few months my therapist was amazing. I wish I hadn't had to move to a different state. You'll get through this
